attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Renesas SH, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ARMv7 ELF binary is classified as malicious and exhibits characteristics of an IoT botnet agent, such as Mirai or Gafgyt. The binary uses direct syscalls and lacks standard imports to evade analysis and maintain portability. Key behaviors include SSDP (Simple Service Discovery Protocol) scanning for network discovery (M-SEARCH to 255.255.255.255:1900) and Layer 7 DDoS capabilities evidenced by a large repository of modern browser User-Agent strings and HTTP GET templates targeting common web paths (/login, /api/status). The entry point (_start) and subroutines show high complexity with manual stack manipulation and obfuscated patterns, typical of malicious packers or custom loaders.
